7. onGoingAuctions - This mapping maps the nft ids with their corresponding auction details.
8. nftsOnAuction - This array keeps track of the nft ids that are on auction.
9. nftIdToAuctionIndex - This mappings keep track of the index at which each nft id in the 
nftsOnAuction array is stored. 
10. blockedAddressToIndex - This mapping keeps track of the index at which the given bloacked
address is stored in the blocked users array.
11. blockedUsers - This array stores the addresses of the blocked users.

blockUser(address).notice: This method is called by the marketplace super admin whenever they find an objectionable user. It prevents the blocked user from connecting again to the marketplace with that address.

buyNftAndChangeOwner(uint256).notice: This method sells the nft to the caller, transfers the ownership and performs the various required manipulations in the businesses, collections and nfts contract.

changeFeePercent(uint256).notice: This method is used to update the fee percent. This method can only be called by the super admin.

changeSuperAdmin(address).notice: This method is used to update the super admin address. This method can only be called by the super admin.

claimNftAndTransferOwnershipAfterAuction.notice: This method is called by the highest bidder of the nft after the completion of the auction. It transfers the ownership to the bidder and performs various required manipulations in the businesses, collections and nfts contract. It also calculates and transfers the marketplace and business fees.

constructor.notice: The following parameters are passed to the constructor at the time of contract creation :- 1. _superAdmin - The address of the super admin. 2. _feeAccount - The account address in which the charged fee is to be deposited. 3. _fee - The fee percentage that is to be charged by the marketplace. 4. nftContractAddress - The address of the deployed NFT contract. 5. collectionsContractAddress - The address of the deployed Collections contract. 6. businessesContractAddress - The address of the deployed Businesses contract.

extendAuction(uint256,uint256).notice: This method extends the bidding period of the particular nft in the auction.

getBalance().notice: This method returns the balance of the fee account.

getBlockedUsers().notice: This method returns a list of user address that are blocked by the marketplace super admin.

getNftAuctionDetails(uint256).notice: This method returns the auction details of the particular nft.

getNftsInAuction().notice: This method returns the ids of all the nfts that are currently in auction.

getTimeLeftInAuctionCompletion(uint256).notice: This method returns the time duration left before the closing of the auction for the particular nft is seconds.

onERC721Received(address,address,uint256.notice: This method is oveeridden in order to create an implementation of the IERC721Receiver.

placeBid(uint256,uint256).notice: This method places a higher bid for a particular nft in the auction.

putAnNftOnAuction(uint256,uint256,uint25.notice: This method puts an nft up in the auction. This method can only be called by the seller  of the nft.

removeNft(uint256).notice: This method is called by the marketplace admin at the time whenever they find an nft objectionable. It removes the nft from the marketplace.

removeUser(address).notice: This method is called by the marketplace super admin whenever they find a suspectible address. It unlists all the nfts and collections owned by that particular address and blocks the address.

superAdmin().notice: 1. superAdmin - The address of the super admin that can be seen by everyone. 2. feeAccount - The account address in which fee is to be deposited for the marketplace. 3. marketplaceFeePercent - The fee percent charged by the marketplace. 4. nftContractInstance - The instance of the nft contract used to call the methods of the same. 5. collectionsContractInstance - The instance of the collections contract used to call the methods of the same. 6. businessesContractInstance - The instance of the businesses contract used to call the methods of the same. 7. onGoingAuctions - This mapping maps the nft ids with their corresponding auction details. 8. nftsOnAuction - This array keeps track of the nft ids that are on auction. 9. nftIdToAuctionIndex - This mappings keep track of the index at which each nft id in the  nftsOnAuction array is stored.  10. blockedAddressToIndex - This mapping keeps track of the index at which the given bloacked address is stored in the blocked users array. 11. blockedUsers - This array stores the addresses of the blocked users.

transferNftBackToOwner(uint256,address).notice: This method is called at the time when an nft is unlisted from the marketplace and the ownership is transfered back to the seller of the NFT.

unblockUser(address).notice: This method is used by the marketplace super admin in order to unblock a blocked address.

updateFeeAccount(address).notice: This method is used to update the fee account address. This method can only be called by the super admin.

withdrawAnNftFromAuction(uint256).notice: This method allows the seller of the nft to withdraw it from the auction.
